text: Shelley Vettese-Baert (born 24 March 1959) is a Canadian taekwondo practitioner. She won the bronze medal at the 1992 Summer Olympics, where taekwondo was a demonstration sport, in the welterweight class. At the 1992 Pan American Taekwondo Championships she won the bronze medal in the -65 kg class. She was a teacher in Edmonton. She held a training camp in Whitecourt. == References == Category:1959 births Category:Taekwondo practitioners Category:Canadian martial artists Category:Living people
